The paper discusses a paradigm for robotic cloud computing, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for converting unstructured data into structured data, which is a common problem in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for effective storage and retrieval of data, which falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The reduction stage of the proposed paradigm involves making sense of massive amounts of data, which is a common problem in Database (cs.DB) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
